\ls6\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}The most important things to know:\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\ls6\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}The 10.3 support is untested at best; sketchy at worst. Test with it thoroughly before you use it.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Sparkle now asks for permission to update on 
\b second launch
\b0 ; don't be surprised at that. You can change that behavior with a delegate method; read SUUpdater.h for more info.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}We no longer distinguish between "check on startup" and "scheduled updates"; everything is scheduled, with the default being every day.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}The test application is using the new profiling features, but that's only for demonstration: these are off by default. More on this later.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}There are no localizations yet.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\ls6\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}New features:\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\ls6\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Sparkle now supports .pkgs. Just name the .pkg the name of the app and put in the update archive.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Sparkle now sends optional demographic profiling information; set SUEnableSystemProfiling to YES in your Info.plist and check out the GET data sent to your webserver when fetching the appcast. More on this in the documentation. The test application has this on so you can see the behavior.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Sparkle now supports updating non-.apps. Just call -setHostBundle: on the global SUUpdater to let it know what you're trying to update.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Sparkle now supports garbage collection in the host app. Use "Sparkle-with-GC.framework" for that, but be aware it's 10.5-only.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Sparkle is now 64-bit compatible, compiling both ppc64 and x86_64.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Sparkle now supports a sparkle:minimumSystemVersion key you can set on appcast items. It does what you think it does.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Sparkle now checks to see if the host app is running from a disk image and refuses to update if it is. (10.4+ only)\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Added support for entities in enclosure paths.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}The file size output is now formatted prettily.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Sparkle now gives visual indication that it's checking for updates when the update's user initiated. ie: it pops up a status controller saying "checking for updates..."\
